  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ENSURING ACCOUNTABILITY &amp; TRANSPARENCY IN CORPORATE-LAND-DEALS FOR LOCAL ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased awareness on the Guidelines for Large Scale Land Acquisitions and improving strong leadership that understand and are informed on land tenure rights and impact on granting large scale land acquisitions for lands based investments in their communities. Local leaders will be fully aware and knowledgeable of legal frameworks that support community rights and social protections, and adhere to transparency and accountability principles with the Ghana guidelines for large scale lands based investments.
Reducing corruption in land administration by empowering the citizens with capacity and information on LSLBI guidelines and principles and other existing legal frameworks to be informed to defend and protect their communal rights on lands and demand fairness, equitable, secured tenure rights, transparency and accountability to end corrupt practices.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The key strategies to be deployed for the project implementation include but not limited to the following;  
-	Partnering with Lands Commission Officials for technical support on the guidelines for Large Scale lands Acquisitions. 
-	Engaging the National and Regional House of Chiefs in their regular meetings to educate and inform them on the provisions of the Guidelines for Large Scale Land Acquisitions. 
-	Creating awareness, Sensitisation and Community Engagement on the Guidelines for Large Scale Land Acquisition and FPIC.  
-	Collaborating with other Institutions, CSOs and Private entities in the development of business models for LSLBI to ensure benefits to local communities are not transitory. 
-	Reviewing how effective and efficient the guidelines would be used and ensuring that the implementation of the guidelines would involve key stakeholders such as Lands Commission, Ministry of Lands and Natural Resources, Ministry of Food and Agriculture, Ministry of Gender and Social Protection, and Parliamentary Select Committees 
-	Media Engagement &#x2013; documenting best practices and success stories and sharing and disseminating innovative practices of communities in short - videos.</narrative>
  </description>
